    {
      "id": "1a76adc5_cb6a221a",
      "file_path": "docs/specs/multicloud_infra_workload.rst",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 43,
      "message": "As Bin shows the future roadmap, CSARS will be distributed to MultiCloud for other plugins such as k8s plugin.\n\nI suggest to add a \"csar_locations:[{key: xxx, value: xxx}]\" parameter to this new API for other plugins if they would like to use CSAR.\n\nThis API now is too heat specified.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 399,
        "name": "Ethan Lynn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "ethanlynnl@vmware.com",
        "username": "ethanlynnl"
      },
      "updated": "2018-08-15 14:04:09.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "1a76adc5_9c6d4e35",
      "file_path": "docs/specs/multicloud_infra_workload.rst",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 40,
      "message": "could VNF module be moved from the multicloud interface and dealed in the SO? Otherwise, this interface will be limited to SO. VNF module concept are not in VFC.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 141,
        "name": "maopeng zhang",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "zhang.maopeng1@zte.com.cn",
        "username": "maopengzhang"
      },
      "updated": "2018-08-16 03:25:04.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "1a76adc5_fc8802e9",
      "file_path": "docs/specs/multicloud_infra_workload.rst",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 81,
      "message": "should we consider a common directives, considering the TOSCA HEAT, TOSCA R2+, even SDNC, etc?\nSuggestions:\ndirectives:[\n  \"id\":\"\"   # unique id of the directives, such as \"oof\" # sdnc,flavor,vnf instance id, etc It is a Must attribute\n  \"attributes\":{#} # it is key-value pair, and be option attribute\n  \"directives\":[....] # it is nested directives, and be option\n]",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 141,
        "name": "maopeng zhang",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "zhang.maopeng1@zte.com.cn",
        "username": "maopengzhang"
      },
      "updated": "2018-08-16 03:25:04.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "1a76adc5_fca48258",
      "file_path": "docs/specs/multicloud_infra_workload.rst",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 40,
      "message": "The association between AAI vserver object and the AAI generic vnf object/VF module object has to be created by somewhere. SO would not be ideal place to do so since it is involved the understanding of hierarchical AAI's cloud region object which is not generic enough so far. And I believe SO has least interest to understand what the schema for the AAI's cloud region object. That's why the heatbridge was done by Robot script in A and B releases. Now MultiCloud could help on that by simply creating this kind of association.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 1889,
        "name": "Bin Yang",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "bin.yang@windriver.com",
        "username": "biny993"
      },
      "updated": "2018-08-16 04:03:03.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "1a76adc5_9c6d4e35",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "1a76adc5_9c89cecc",
      "file_path": "docs/specs/multicloud_infra_workload.rst",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 81,
      "message": "MultiCloud is flexible on whatever the json schema is. Maybe Srini/Marcus has some reason for this proposal. You may also put your comment at wiki: https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/SO+Casablanca+HPA+Design",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 1889,
        "name": "Bin Yang",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "bin.yang@windriver.com",
        "username": "biny993"
      },
      "updated": "2018-08-16 04:03:03.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "1a76adc5_fc8802e9",
      "unresolved": false
    },
